---
source: src/core/capabilities.rs, Cargo.toml
assertion: serve adapter is feature-gated and unavailable in default build
schema:
  feature: serve
  status: feature_disabled
contracts:
  - serve feature enables optional HTTP adapter for localhost access
  - default build does not include serve feature
  - serve feature must not pull tokio, hyper, axum, tower, or reqwest into default tree
  - when serve feature disabled, capabilities report serve as unavailable
  - serve adapter wraps existing CLI commands, does not add business logic
  - localhost-only boundary enforced (no public network exposure)
  - read-only or explicitly audited mutations
  - JSON responses mirror CLI contracts
  - HTTP endpoints follow ee_ naming convention from MCP tools
feature_requirements:
  - serve = [] feature flag in Cargo.toml
  - BuildFeature::new("serve", cfg!(feature = "serve")) in capabilities
  - FeatureEntry::new("serve", cfg!(feature = "serve"), "HTTP serve adapter")
  - forbidden dependencies not pulled: tokio, hyper, axum, tower, reqwest
  - no CLI command surface when feature disabled (adapter-only)
evidence:
  - Cargo.toml: serve = []
  - src/core/mod.rs: BuildFeature::new("serve", cfg!(feature = "serve"))
  - src/core/capabilities.rs: FeatureEntry for serve
  - status --json includes serve in features array with enabled: false
degraded_contract:
  - serve surface unavailable in default build
  - capabilities.features reports serve.enabled = false
  - no HTTP server starts without explicit feature enablement
